      • getInstance

        public static UserCache getInstance(java.io.File file,
                                    org.shanerx.faketrollplus.FakeTrollPlus ftp)
        Constructs the UserCache object.
        The class follows the singleton pattern. No more than one instance should be created.
        The software is not liable for any damages caused by accessing the storage file in an asynchronous way nor by different instances.
        Parameters:
        file - the File where the data is saved.
        ftp - the current Plugin instance.
        Returns:
        the current instance of the class.

      • getUserCacheFile

        public java.io.File getUserCacheFile()
        Gets the file object representing the actual file where the user information is stored.
        Equivalent to {@link java.io.File} = new {@link java.io.File}({@link org.shanerx.faketrollplus.FakeTrollPlus#getDataFolder()}, "usercache.json");
        The plugin will automatically (re-)generate the file.
        Returns:
        the File object representing the file on the disk where the data is saved.

      • getPlayerInfo

        public org.json.simple.JSONObject getPlayerInfo(java.util.UUID uuid)
        Returns an instance of JSONObject, containing the specific data related to that UUID.
        null if there are no records about that player. If the value null is returned, the player may still have joined once, they have never been trolled.
        Parameters:
        uuid - the uuid of the player.
        Returns:
        the JSONObject representing the data related to the UUID.
